# ğŸ©¸ Cancer LLM â€“ Blood Cancer Prognosis Dataset Builder

This project automatically collects **prognosis, survival, and outcome-related research articles** for major blood cancer types from **PubMed Central (PMC)** and prepares a clean text dataset for **Medical LLM training**.

It downloads full-text XML articles, extracts meaningful content (title, abstract, body), cleans the text, and saves everything into one unified dataset folder.

---

## ğŸ¯ Purpose

To build a **large-scale prognosis-focused dataset** covering all major blood cancers for:

* Medical Large Language Model (LLM) training
* Survival prediction research
* Outcome analysis
* Clinical AI development
* Oncology NLP tasks

---

## ğŸ§¬ Covered Blood Cancer Types

The script collects articles for:

* Acute Myeloid Leukemia (AML)
* Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia (ALL)
* Chronic Myeloid Leukemia (CML)
* Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia (CLL)
* Hodgkin Lymphoma
* Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma
* Diffuse Large B-Cell Lymphoma (DLBCL)
* Follicular Lymphoma
* Multiple Myeloma
* Plasmacytoma
* Myelodysplastic Syndrome (MDS)
* Myeloproliferative Neoplasm (MPN)

Each cancer type can collect up to **500 articles** (default), totaling approximately **6,000 research papers**.

